<h1>Letter Before Claim</h1>

<hr>

<p><strong>Date:</strong> {{generation_date}}</p>

<p>
<strong>To:</strong><br>
{{tenant_full_name}}<br>
{{#if tenant_2_name}}{{tenant_2_name}}<br>{{/if}}
{{property_address}}<br>
{{property_postcode}}
</p>

<p>
<strong>From:</strong><br>
{{landlord_full_name}}<br>
{{#if landlord_2_name}}{{landlord_2_name}}<br>{{/if}}
{{landlord_address}}<br>
{{landlord_postcode}}
</p>

{{#if solicitor_firm}}
<p>
<strong>Via:</strong><br>
{{solicitor_firm}}<br>
{{solicitor_address}}<br>
Reference: {{claimant_reference}}
</p>
{{/if}}

<hr>

<h2>LETTER OF CLAIM - UNPAID RENT AND ARREARS</h2>

<p>Dear {{tenant_full_name}},</p>

<h3>Re: Property at {{property_address}}</h3>

<p>
I am writing to you about the money I say you owe in connection with the above property. This letter
is sent in accordance with the <strong>Pre-Action Protocol for Debt Claims</strong>. It sets out:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>the amount claimed;</li>
  <li>what the debt is said to cover;</li>
  <li>how the figure has been calculated;</li>
  <li>what you can do next; and</li>
  <li>what may happen if you do not reply or pay.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1. Summary of the Debt</h3>

<table border="1" cellpadding="8" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Rent arrears:</strong></td>
    <td align="right">{{currency arrears_total}}</td>
  </tr>
  {{#if damages_total}}
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Property damage / other costs:</strong></td>
    <td align="right">{{currency damages_total}}</td>
  </tr>
  {{/if}}
  {{#if other_total}}
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Other charges:</strong></td>
    <td align="right">{{currency other_total}}</td>
  </tr>
  {{/if}}
  {{#if claim_interest}}
  <tr>
    <td><strong>Interest to date ({{interest_rate}}% per annum):</strong></td>
    <td align="right">{{currency interest_to_date}}</td>
  </tr>
  {{/if}}
  <tr style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
    <td><strong>TOTAL AMOUNT OWED:</strong></td>
    <td align="right"><strong>{{currency total_claim_amount}}</strong></td>
  </tr>
</table>

{{#if claim_interest}}
<p><em>Interest continues to accrue at {{currency daily_interest}} per day until the debt is paid in full.</em></p>
{{/if}}

<h3>2. Breakdown of the Debt</h3>

<h4>Rent Arrears</h4>
<p>
You occupy the property under an assured shorthold tenancy that commenced on {{tenancy_start_date}}. The agreed rent is {{currency rent_amount}} {{rent_frequency}}, payable in advance.
</p>

<p>
You have failed to pay rent as it fell due. The arrears have accumulated over multiple rent periods. A detailed schedule showing each period, the amount due, what you paid, and the balance is attached as <strong>Appendix 1</strong>.
</p>

{{#if damage_items.length}}
<h4>Property Damage and Other Costs</h4>
<p>In addition to rent arrears, you are liable for the following:</p>
<ul>
  {{#each damage_items}}
  <li>{{description}} - {{currency amount}}</li>
  {{/each}}
</ul>
{{/if}}

{{#if other_charges.length}}
<h4>Other Recoverable Charges</h4>
<ul>
  {{#each other_charges}}
  <li>{{description}} - {{currency amount}}</li>
  {{/each}}
</ul>
{{/if}}

{{#if claim_interest}}
<h4>Interest</h4>
<p>
I am entitled to claim interest on the outstanding rent and costs pursuant to <strong>section 69 of the County Courts Act 1984</strong>. Interest is calculated at {{interest_rate}}% per annum from {{interest_start_date}} and continues to accrue at {{currency daily_interest}} per day until payment.
</p>

<p>
The interest calculation to {{generation_date}} is {{currency interest_to_date}}. The full working is attached as <strong>Appendix 2</strong>.
</p>
{{/if}}

<h3>3. What You Must Do Now</h3>

<p>
You have <strong>30 days from the date of this letter</strong> (i.e., until {{response_deadline}}) to do ONE of the following:
</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Pay the full amount owed</strong> ({{currency total_claim_amount}}) to avoid court proceedings.</li>
  <li><strong>Contact me to discuss a payment arrangement</strong> if you cannot pay in full.</li>
  <li><strong>Complete the enclosed Reply Form</strong> if you dispute the debt or need time to seek advice.</li>
</ol>

<h4>Payment Methods</h4>
<p>
If you wish to pay the debt in full, please arrange payment by bank transfer using the details below.
</p>
{{#if has_bank_transfer_details}}
<ul>
  <li>Account name: {{payment_account_name}}</li>
  <li>Sort code: {{payment_sort_code}}</li>
  <li>Account number: {{payment_account_number}}</li>
  <li>Payment reference: {{payment_reference}}</li>
</ul>
{{else}}
<p>
Please contact me using the details shown at the top of this letter to obtain the bank transfer details. Quote
<strong>{{payment_reference}}</strong> when making payment.
</p>
{{/if}}

<p>
If you need to discuss payment, use the contact details shown at the top of this letter.
</p>

<h4>Payment Plans</h4>
<p>
If you cannot pay the full amount but can make regular payments, I may be willing to consider a
payment arrangement. You must contact me within 30 days with a realistic proposal. Any offer must:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Clear the arrears within a reasonable time (typically 6-12 months);</li>
  <li>Include ongoing rent payments in full;</li>
  <li>Be supported by evidence of your income and expenditure.</li>
</ul>

<p>
Please complete the enclosed <strong>Financial Statement Form</strong> if you wish to propose a payment plan.
</p>

<h3>4. Sources of Free Debt Advice</h3>

<p>
If you are unsure what to do, you can get free, independent debt advice from:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Citizens Advice:</strong> 0800 144 8848 or <a href="https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk">www.citizensadvice.org.uk</a></li>
  <li><strong>StepChange Debt Charity:</strong> 0800 138 1111 or <a href="https://www.stepchange.org">www.stepchange.org</a></li>
  <li><strong>National Debtline:</strong> 0808 808 4000 or <a href="https://www.nationaldebtline.org">www.nationaldebtline.org</a></li>
  <li><strong>MoneyHelper:</strong> 0800 138 7777 or <a href="https://www.moneyhelper.org.uk">www.moneyhelper.org.uk</a></li>
</ul>

<p><em>These services are free and confidential. They can help you understand your options and, if needed, contact me on your behalf.</em></p>

<h3>5. What Happens If You Do Not Respond or Pay</h3>

<p>
If you do not respond to this letter within 30 days, or if you do not make acceptable arrangements to pay, I will have no choice but to issue court proceedings against you without further warning.
</p>

<p><strong>If I issue a court claim, I will ask the court for:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>the full amount owed ({{currency total_claim_amount}}) together with <strong>court fees and any recoverable costs</strong>;</li>
  <li>the court fee, which is currently about {{currency court_fee}};</li>
  {{#if solicitor_costs}}<li>If I instruct solicitors, you may also be liable for legal costs of {{currency solicitor_costs}} or more.</li>{{/if}}
  {{#if claim_interest}}<li>continuing interest at {{currency daily_interest}} per day until payment or judgment;</li>{{/if}}
  <li>a County Court Judgment, which can affect your credit record for six years if it is not paid in time; and</li>
  <li>enforcement action if needed, such as bailiffs, an attachment of earnings order, or a charging order.</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>It is in your best interests to contact me now to resolve this matter.</strong>
</p>

<h3>6. Documents Enclosed</h3>

<p>The following documents are enclosed with this letter:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Information Sheet for Defendants</li>
  <li>Reply Form</li>
  <li>Financial Statement Form</li>
  <li>Appendix 1: Schedule of Rent Arrears</li>
  {{#if claim_interest}}<li>Appendix 2: Interest Calculation</li>{{/if}}
</ol>

<h3>7. Your Rights</h3>

<p>
You have the right to:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Seek free debt advice from the organisations listed above;</li>
  <li>Dispute the debt if you believe it is wrong;</li>
  <li>Ask for more information or documents;</li>
  <li>Propose a payment plan if you cannot pay in full;</li>
  <li>Defend any court claim if you have a valid legal defence.</li>
</ul>

<p>
<strong>Please do not ignore this letter.</strong> If you need time, documents, or debt advice, use the Reply Form and let me know within 30 days.
</p>

<hr>

<p>Yours sincerely,</p>

<p>
{{signatory_name}}<br>
{{#if solicitor_firm}}{{solicitor_firm}}<br>{{/if}}
Date: {{signature_date}}
</p>

<hr>

<p><em><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> This is a formal Letter Before Claim sent under the Pre-Action Protocol for Debt Claims. You should reply within 30 days. If you do not reply or pay, court proceedings may be started without further notice.</em></p>
